Name Description

Example

Query
query BulkUpdateScriptChanges(
  $organizationId: String!,
  $findAndReplace: BulkUpdateScriptInput!
) {
  bulkUpdateScriptChanges(
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    findAndReplace: $findAndReplace
  ) {
    id
    campaignId
    campaignName
    script
  }
}
Variables
{
  "organizationId": "abc123",
  "findAndReplace": BulkUpdateScriptInput
}
Response

  "data": {
    "bulkUpdateScriptChanges": [
      {
        "id": "abc123",
        "campaignId": "xyz789",
        "campaignName": "abc123",
        "script": "xyz789"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Queries

campaignGroups

Response

Returns a CampaignGroupPage!

Arguments
Name Description
organizationId - String!
after - Cursor
first - Int

Example

Query
query CampaignGroups(
  $organizationId: String!,
  $after: Cursor,
  $first: Int
) {
  campaignGroups(
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    after: $after,
    first: $first
  ) {
    edges {
      cursor
      node {
        ...CampaignGroupFragment
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      totalCount
      hasNextPage
      hasPreviousPage
      startCursor
      endCursor
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "organizationId": "xyz789",
  "after": Cursor,
  "first": 123
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "campaignGroups": {
      "edges": [CampaignGroupEdge],
      "pageInfo": RelayPageInfo
    }
  }
}

Queries

campaigns

Response

Returns a CampaignsReturn

Arguments
Name Description
organizationId - String!
cursor - OffsetLimitCursor
campaignsFilter - CampaignsFilter

Example

Query
query Campaigns(
  $organizationId: String!,
  $cursor: OffsetLimitCursor,
  $campaignsFilter: CampaignsFilter
) {
  campaigns(
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    cursor: $cursor,
    campaignsFilter: $campaignsFilter
  ) {
    ... on PaginatedCampaigns {
      campaigns {
        ...CampaignFragment
      }
      pageInfo {
        ...PageInfoFragment
      }

Query
query People(
  $organizationId: String,
  $cursor: OffsetLimitCursor,
  $campaignsFilter: CampaignsFilter,
  $role: String,
  $userIds: [String]
) {
  people(
    organizationId: $organizationId,
    cursor: $cursor,
    campaignsFilter: $campaignsFilter,
    role: $role,
    userIds: $userIds
  ) {
    ... on PaginatedUsers {
      users {
        ...UserFragment
      }
      pageInfo {
        ...PageInfoFragment
      }
    }
    ... on UsersList {
      users {
        ...UserFragment
      }
    }
  }
}

Types

Float

Description

The Float scalar type represents signed double-precision fractional values as specified by IEEE 754.

Example
123.45
Types

FoundContact

Fields
Field Name Description
found - Boolean
Example
{"found": false}
Types

ID

Description

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
4
Types

Int

Description

The Int scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

Example
987
